<DocsLayout title="Dispatch Overview" section="Dispatch">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Dispatching is the backbone of efficient service operations, ensuring the right resources
    are in the right place at the right time. Field Promax offers multiple calendar views
    to manage work orders effectively.
  </p>
  <p>
    Whether it's Day, Week, Work Week, or Month view, you can quickly adapt to the format
    that suits your needs. With drag-and-drop functionality, filters, and color-coded schedules,
    managing assignments has never been easier.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>From the left panel, select <strong>Dispatch</strong> and choose any calendar view</li>
    <li>To customize calendar settings: <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Company</strong> → <strong>Calendar Settings</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Calendar Features</h2>

  <h3>Create Work Orders</h3>
  <p>Double-click anywhere on the calendar to quickly create a new work order.</p>

  <h3>Schedules (Visits)</h3>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/schedulingoverview_01.webp" alt="Schedules on Calendar" />
  <p>
    Each schedule represents a visit. Schedules are color-coded by technician.
    A work order may appear multiple times if it has multiple schedules.
  </p>

  <h3>Calendar Views</h3>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/schedulingoverview_02.webp" alt="Calendar Views" />
  <p>Switch between views to display work orders in your preferred format:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Day View:</strong> Detailed hourly breakdown</li>
    <li><strong>Week View:</strong> Full 7-day overview</li>
    <li><strong>Work Week View:</strong> Monday through Friday</li>
    <li><strong>Month View:</strong> High-level monthly overview</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Filters</h3>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/schedulingoverview_03.webp" alt="Calendar Filters" />
  <p>
    Use the orange filter button to adjust which work orders you see.
    Filter by technician, work group, and more. Expand the left panel for filter options.
  </p>

  <h3>Drag and Drop</h3>
  <p>
    Drag and drop schedules to easily reassign them to a different technician
    or change the date and time.
  </p>

  <h3>Status Indicators</h3>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/schedulingoverview_04.webp" alt="Completed Schedules" />
  <img src="/images/dispatch/schedulingoverview_05.webp" alt="Closed Orders" />
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Completed Schedules:</strong> Marked with a checkbox</li>
    <li><strong>Closed Orders:</strong> Marked with a checkbox and strikethrough</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Days Off</h3>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/schedulingoverview_06.webp" alt="Days Off" />
  <p>
    Technician days off are displayed on the calendar to prevent accidental scheduling
    during unavailable times.
  </p>

  <h3>Unassigned Work Orders</h3>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/schedulingoverview_07.webp" alt="Unassigned Work Orders" />
  <p>
    Unassigned work orders appear in the left panel. Drag and drop them to assign
    to a technician.
  </p>

  <h3>Calendar Customization</h3>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/schedulingoverview_08.webp" alt="Calendar Settings" />
  <p>
    Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Company</strong> → <strong>Calendar Settings</strong>
    to configure business hours and other preferences.
  </p>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Technicians</strong> receive text messages when work orders are assigned</li>
    <li><strong>Administrators</strong> have full access to all calendar features and settings</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Customize your calendar settings</strong> to match your business hours and technician availability.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Use filters</strong> to focus on specific technicians or work groups.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Monitor completed and closed orders</strong> to ensure timely invoicing and follow-up.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
